Here's a complete implementation:

```csharp
// In Program.cs

// Configure Kestrel and form size limits
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(o => o.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 11 * 1024 * 1024);
builder.Services.Configure<FormOptions>(o =>
{
    o.MultipartBodyLengthLimit = 10 * 1024 * 1024;
});

var app = builder.Build();

// Ensure uploads directory exists
var uploadsPath = Path.Combine(app.Environment.ContentRootPath, "uploads");
Directory.CreateDirectory(uploadsPath);

app.MapPost("/upload", async (IFormFile file) =>
{
    // Validate size (defense-in-depth; FormOptions already enforces this)
    if (file.Length > 10 * 1024 * 1024)
        return Results.BadRequest("File exceeds 10 MB limit.");

    // Validate content type
    string[] allowed = ["image/jpeg", "image/png"];
    if (!allowed.Contains(file.ContentType, StringComparer.OrdinalIgnoreCase))
        return Results.BadRequest("Only JPEG and PNG files are accepted.");

    // Generate a safe, unique filename preserving the original extension
    var ext = file.ContentType == "image/png" ? ".png" : ".jpg";
    var fileName = $"{Guid.NewGuid()}{ext}";
    var filePath = Path.Combine(uploadsPath, fileName);

    await using var stream = File.Create(filePath);
    await file.CopyToAsync(stream);

    return Results.Ok(new { fileName });
})
.DisableAntiforgery()       // required for API clients sending multipart/form-data
.DisableRequestSizeLimit()  // let our own FormOptions limit govern instead of the default 30 MB body cap
.WithName("UploadImage");
```

**Key points:**

- **`FormOptions.MultipartBodyLengthLimit`** is the real gate — it rejects oversized parts before buffering the full file.
- **Content-type check** uses the MIME type from the `Content-Type` header of the multipart part. For stronger validation, read the first bytes (magic numbers) of the stream.
- **`DisableAntiforgery()`** is needed per-endpoint because your pipeline calls `UseAntiforgery()`; without it, API clients (Postman, mobile apps) will get 400s since they won't send the antiforgery token.
- **`Guid` filenames** prevent path-traversal and collision from user-supplied names.
